Case No. 3,697. DEAKINS v. LEE. [1 Cranch, C. C. 442.] 1 Circuit Court, District of Columbia. July Term, 1807. [This was an action by Deakins v. Lee, special bail for McCarty Fitzliugh.]

Practice axd Pi.eat)ixg.

The court will permit the defendant to withdraw the general issue and file a general demurrer.

E. J. Lee prayed leave to withdraw the plea of nul tiel record, and to demur generally. Granted, and judgment on the demurrer in favor of the plaintiff.
